SQUASHING MYTHS ABOUT WEIGHT TRAINING! ü§îüëäüèºü§Øüí™üèºüòé
‚†Ä‚†Ä
1Ô∏è‚É£ Muscle weighs more than fat - Muscle is twice as dense than fat, so it takes up LESS space ‚òùüèº BUT there is no difference in weight.
‚†Ä‚†Ä
2Ô∏è‚É£ Heavy weight, low reps will make you bulky.‚Ä®- Since fat takes up more space than muscle, technically it‚Äôs your NUTRITION that makes you look ‚Äúbulky‚Äù ü§≠ However different desired physiques do involve a different style of training.
‚†Ä‚†Ä
3Ô∏è‚É£ High reps low weight is best for girls/toning.‚Ä®- If you want to look ‚Äútoned‚Äù You need to build a foundation of muscle in order to create the look of a tight, shapely physique. To build muscle you need to lift weights and challenge yourself to create a progressive overload with resistance. Larger muscles take more force (weight) to build, like the glutes. So no, it‚Äôs not all about lower weight high rep. I prefer a combination of both! 2 heavy compound exercises with higher rep for accessory movements.
‚†Ä‚†Ä
4Ô∏è‚É£ You cant grow the glutes without leg development.‚Ä®It is impossible ü§≠ YES -  There are exercises you can do for more glute ISOLATION and less quad/hamstring (Hip Thrusts), but you are training the legs as a biproduct of training the glutes! That is where the strength is coming from. If you could not use your legs, you cannot train the glutes üôáüèª‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏èYou don‚Äôt want to be unsymmetrical though ladies, so it‚Äôs important to have developed legs as well!
‚†Ä‚†Ä
5Ô∏è‚É£ Cardio to lose weight, then weight training?‚Ä®- Weight training and building lean muscle tissue will transform your physique and build up your metabolism in ways cardio alone cannot ‚ÄºÔ∏è When people opt for cardio they are ultimately looking to create a larger calorie deficit to help with weight loss. But when looking to lose weight instead of ramping up the cardio, hone in on your DIET! You can actually make progress with no cardio at ALL, IF your nutrition is on point!
‚†Ä‚†Ä

‚†Ä‚†Ä
As long as you are HEALTHY and not carrying around a lot of excess weight (that could eventually lead to health problems) - the number that shows up on the scale means absolutely NOTHING!
